Imperial Secret Agent Alicia: Lord Rex! I'm glad you're
safe...!
Prince Rex: You... just what...

Imperial Secret Agent Alicia: I am Alicia from the Imperial
Secret Agency, and I believe that Prince Rex is the rightful
king.
Prince Rex: Am I the rightful... king...?

Imperial Secret Agent Alicia: The pursuers are coming!
Please wait, I will release you from the [cage] immediately.
Prince Rex: ...Thank you for coming to rescue me.
Prince Rex: I will believe in you and follow you.

Rex was in despair. Just as the sun has a great influence
simply by existing, Rex also has a great influence simply by
existing.

The faction that recognizes Prince Rex as the legitimate
heir went to great lengths to rescue Rex, who was imprisoned
by Caron. Naturally, there were numerous casualties and much
bloodshed on both sides.

Rex was in despair because he understood that every drop of
flowing blood was happening because of his own existence.

Just as I was thinking that I wouldn't mind decaying here
with the monsters... a woman claiming to be from the
Imperial Secret Agency came to my rescue. In my weakened and
hazy state, one word strongly shook my heart.

Liberation from the Cage--I heard the sound of the cage in
my heart creaking. Sharp claws reaching through the gaps in
the cage. The claws of a monster, denied by everything,
touch Rex.

And slowly, they gouge out Rex's flesh. Strangely, there is
no pain, only a strong sensation of heat.

The monster speaks to Rex with a laugh. Even if you don't
break the cage yourself, someone will definitely break your
cage. Faster than you think, slower than your entourage
thinks, and so on.
